 'Writers Session Wrangelstraße 25 10997 Berlin  - zum Stadtplan Einschränkung: To get in for free, use the code “GRATIS BERLIN” Jeden Montag\n - Anfangszeit: 16:00 Uhr Kategorie: Leute treffen DNA. present "Writers Session" an Open Platform to learn to edit receive, give & to grow. Together. \u200dIn this context, "Writes Session" means we are bringing in different writing styles and helping each other improve through drafting, receiving and giving feedback. Showcase the best version of Your writing, as we provide a Safe Space for Writing of all kinds (including prose, poetry, essay\'s etc.) and for Writers of all Levels. \u200dWriters of all kinds & all Styles are welcome. \u200dThis event is all about bringing storytellers, poets, writers, essayists, screenwriters and creative minds into a shared space where they can draft each-others work and receive positive as well as critical feedback in an encouraging manner. \u200d\u200dEvery respectful Person is welcome to join. \u200d\u200dWHEN: Every Monday DOORS: 4 pm START: 4.30 pm END: 6 pm\u200d\u200d WHERE: DNA. Art House Wrangelstraße 25, 10997 Berlin\u200d TICKETS: 5 Euro Whether You\'re there to show off Your skills or simply soak up the creative atmosphere, this is Your opportunity to be part of something special. Take the chance to join the Writers Session and see where Your passion can take You. \u200d\u200dDRAFTING GUIDELINES: Encouraging feedback before criticism. “This and this was great, do more of it. I would also work on this etc.” We could be working with sensitive pieces. Include trigger warnings. We want people to benefit and grow their pieces from our workshops. Creating a safe space to encourage vulnerable. \u200d\u200dSTRUCTURE:\u200d People will have a chance to enter their names to book a slot to draft each week. We need to know who is presenting 1 or 2 days before they do. Session Length: 1hr 30 minutes 6 people drafting 12 people giving feedback 20 minutes for each draft 5 minutes reading + explaining text intention 5 minutes drafting (each individual, ink to the page) 5 - 10 minutes feedback 12 copies given back to the author w/feedback 20minutes x 6people = 1hour 20 minutes +-10 minutes for longer/shorter pieces text A 5-minute break after 45 minutes. People bring their drafts: poetry, prose even spoken word etc. \u200d\u200dSTEPS TO PERFORM: SIGN UP 1. To present Your pieces ONLY 6 slots available to present Your pieces. 2. To attend as a feedback giver and get priority to present Your pieces the following session. \u200d\u200dSIGN UP: Sign up below & Save Your Drafting Spot. For more info see: www.dna-artclub.com / follow us on IG: @nightart.club :) \u200d\u200dSee Us Soon. Love. DNA. von: DNA. Mehr Infos im Internet: https://www.dna-artclub.com',
 'Montags Standup Comedy auf Englisch neben Ostkreuz Lenbachstr. 17 10245 Berlin  - zum Stadtplan Jeden Montag\n - Anfangszeit: 19:30 Uhr Kategorie: Comedy & Theater RESERVE FREE SEAT HERE:\xa0https://www.eventbrite.com/e/the-kooks-nest-comedy-open-mic-oct-14-tickets-1042884635017?aff=ebdsoporgprofile Mondays suck, but these kooky comedians are here to save the day. You wanna have a funky funny time after a stressful beginning to your work week? Come on down to Berlin\'s coolest new bar “The Brazen Squirrel” right by Ostkreuz and enjoy this brand new curated comedy Open-Mic, brought to you and hosted by some of Berlins kookiest newcomers Felix Mangold (@fxmgd_) and Tom Strissel (@tomstrisselcomedy). See anything from a beginner loosing their comedy virginity to a professional international comedian fine-tuning their best jokes while slurping on The Brazen Squirrel\'s incredible assortment of drinks. This is live performance, this is live comedy, this is art, this is going to be kooky, this is The Kooks Nest Comedy Open Mic @ The Brazen Squirrel. Anything can happen. Oh I forgot, there\'s also video games. LOCATION: The Brazen Squirrel, Lenbachstr. 17, 10245 Berlin - 3 min walk from Ostkreuz S HOW MUCH: FREE but we accept donations ;) HOSTS: Tom Strissel: @tomstrisselcomedy - Born and raised in the US, Tom moved to Germany in the fall of 2022 and has been performing standup since the spring of 2023. He was a semi-finalist in the 2024 Berlin New Standup Award and is a recurring member of the Berlin-based sketch comedy group "Fuster Clucks". He is also the winner of the 2016 WBIN Family Guy Impression Contest. No one knows what that is, and you probably won\'t find anything about it online, but it was totally a thing. People were there. Felix Mangold: @fxmgd_Starting out in the Amsterdam Comedy Scene back in 2021, Felix has been equally dazzling and weirding out Berlin Comedy audiences since his move here in 2022 and quick detour to a psychiatric hospital in 2023. Off weed and high on lexapro since then, he’s been trying to perfect his abstract, dark and stupid stage presence and jokes. For good and bad, he is definitely unlike any other comedian in Berlin. According to Oxford English Dictionary:kook (noun) a mad or eccentric person. von: kooksnestcomedy Mehr Infos im Internet: https://www.eventbrite.com',
